                 <h3> Explain Me Please I Am A Nerd </h3>
                <p> First of all, whenever a new protocol or cryptocurrency comes out in the blockchain space, the founders normally write what is called a whitepaper. A whitepaper is a document which outlines the problem, solution, product, implementation, and more of a new protol or currency. You should always look for a whitepaper when new technology in the blockchain space is released so you can quickly get up to speed. Here is Bitcoin's <a href="https://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf" target="blank">Whitepaper</a> by Satoshi Nakamoto.</p>
                <p> If you are a developer, a great resource to learn how to start developing on the Bitcoin blockchain is the <a href="https://bitcoin.org/en/developer-documentation" target="blank"> Bitcoin Developer Documentation</a>. </p>
                <p> One of the best books about Bitcoin technology is  <a href="https://github.com/bitcoinbook/bitcoinbook" target="blank"> Mastering Bitcoin </a> by Andreas Antonopolous. It is very hightly rated and covers all aspects of Bitcoin in detail.</p>
